    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-06-13T17:43:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-06-13T17:43:00-05:00" n="5"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d5">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">310/6–1352: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting United States Representative at the United
                        Nations</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GROSSEA1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gross</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-06-13T18:43:00-04:00"
                            >June 13, 1952—6:43 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>933. Re US–<gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss> talks on <gloss target="#t_UN1"
                        >UN</gloss> problems. Appreciate info <gloss target="#t_Deptel1"
                        >Deptel</gloss> 469, June 4, and authority to comply with <persName
                        corresp="#p_JEBBSHMG1">Jebb</persName>’s request for informal discussions
                    here re basic attitudes of <gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss> toward US and
                        <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss>. As <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss>
                    aware, <persName corresp="#p_JEBBSHMG1">Jebb</persName> in series recent public
                    speeches—notably at Syracuse, Dallas and Chicago—has been expounding thesis
                    which has been regarded by many as minimizing <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss>
                    present and potential collective security role while stressing concept <gloss
                        target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> as “universal” forum which might be useful to
                    “conciliate” East/West differences.</p>
                <p>I am aware from reftel that <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> contemplates
                    conversations with Brit possibly in Sept, which will enable <gloss
                        target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> to test US general <pb facs="0037" n="9"
                        xml:id="pg_9"/> principles by discussion of specific items. Talks with
                        <persName corresp="#p_JEBBSHMG1">Jebb</persName> would accordingly be
                    general as well as “preliminary and informal.” However, general discussions of
                    sort <persName corresp="#p_JEBBSHMG1">Jebb</persName> has in mind may
                    necessarily involve some particularly on issues such as membership, <gloss
                        target="#t_CMC1">CMC</gloss> future, etc. In order to make certain we
                    understand what <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> has in mind, and to avoid
                    risk of prematurity and confusion, I would be grateful if <gloss
                        target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> would give us general guidance for
                    discussions in accordance with offer in reftel.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GROSSEA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gross</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
